 <!-- Introduction -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of the data that identify qualifications and the association of qualifications with
     a person or organization. Qualifications are a definitive recognition of achievement as a
     practitioner with the level of qualification normally shown by certification. Qualifications are
     usually gained through the passing of an examination or the completion of a training course.
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>The identification of qualifications;</li>
   <li>The association of qualifications with a person or an organization.</li>
 </inscope>

